Manchester City manager, Pep Guardiola, has insisted that the club has not received any approach for Mikel Arteta. Speaking to reporters on Friday ahead of the Manchester Derby this Sunday, Guardiola insisted that Arteta could succeed him as manager if he remains at the Etihad. Arteta is one of the bookmakers’ favourites to replace Unai Emery as Arsenal head coach and has also been linked with the vacant Everton job. “He travelled to Burnley (on Tuesday) and tomorrow he will be close to me again against United. “He will be here until the end of the season, I think so,” Guardiola said. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.